Stephen King On Getting Scared: 'Nothing Like Your First Time'Doctor Sleep by Stephen King Hardcover, 531 pages | purchase close overlay Buy Featured Book Your purchase helps support NPR programming.
"Being scared is like sex," Stephen King says.
For a lot of readers, King's 1977 horror novel The Shining may have been their first fictional scare.
Now, nearly four decades later, King picks up Danny's story as an adult in the novel's sequel, Doctor Sleep.
King tells Greene that revisiting such a celebrated horror story was no small challenge.